    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-24T15:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-24T15:41:00-05:00" n="799"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d799">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19640</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-24T14:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Revolutionists becoming very active south and west of Tampico. Reported to have
                    captured and looted Ozuluama and defeated <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> troops
                    near Grandler English petroleum well at Potrero, from whence Englishmen were
                    warned away a week ago by Carranza troops. Rebels lately raided (?) and
                    threatened Panuco.</p>
                <p>All reports agree country is passing into worst state of anarchy yet known, with
                    Government more impotent than ever to prevent it. It is believed now is
                    opportune time to augment our naval forces here to meet any emergency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
